# /etc/default/grub — CM5 UEFI additions
# DTB is handled by /etc/grub.d/10_rpi5_dtb — do NOT set GRUB_DTB here
# Setting GRUB_DTB here overrides grub.d scripts and breaks the fallback chain

GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="quiet rd.driver.post=metis rd.driver.post=rtl8365mb"
# rd.driver.post: modprobed after udev settles in initramfs
# metis: Axelera AIPU — needs DT PCIe node to exist first
# rtl8365mb: DSA switch — needs cruiser overlay applied first

# Serial console for CM5 debug (RP1 UART, not ttyAMA0)
# GRUB_TERMINAL="serial console"
# GRUB_SERIAL_COMMAND="serial --unit=0 --speed=115200"

GRUB_TIMEOUT=3
GRUB_DEFAULT=0
```

---

**The full boot sequence on your UEFI CM5:**
```
EEPROM → RPI_EFI.fd
    │
    └─ config.txt: armstub= + pciex1=on only
           │
           └─ UEFI hands off to GRUB (EFI partition)
                  │
                  └─ grub.d/10_rpi5_dtb: devicetree bcm2712-rpi-cm5.dtb
                         │
                         └─ kernel loads → dracut initramfs
                                │
                                └─ initqueue/settled:
                                       apply-overlays.sh
                                       ├─ mount configfs
                                       ├─ cat cruiser.dtbo → overlays/cruiser/dtbo
                                       ├─ modprobe rtl8365mb  ← DSA switch
                                       ├─ modprobe hci_uart   ← BT
                                       └─ modprobe metis      ← AIPU
                                              │
                                              └─ pivot_root → real system
